sections.text:
Input: A family of distinct partitions, represented by a sorted list P = [p1, . . . , pn]: pi 6= pj, for all i 6= j, and |p1| ≤ . . . ≤ |pn|;
Output: The conceptual hierarchy as a DAG, represented by the n by n adjacency matrix T: T[i, j] = 1 if there is an edge from node i to node j in the DAG;
initialize T[i, j] = 0 for all i, j; for i = n : 1 do
for j = (i + 1) : n do if T[i, j] == 0 then
if is coarser(pi, pj) then for k in {k | pj ≺ pk} ∪ {j} do
T[i, k] = 1; end
end end
end end T = Transpose(T);
Algorithm 1: Algorithm for computing the conceptual hierarchy
